 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of characteristics that can be assigned to a work output, 
     such as identifiers, approvals, and security classification.
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>the identification of work output;</li>
   <li>the association of approvals, certifications, dates,  times, people, and organizations to work output;</li>
   <li>the association of properties to work output;</li>
   <li>the association of work output to an entry in a work management scheme;</li>
   <li>the security classification of work output.</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>the quantity of work that is output;</li>
   <li>the relationships between activity outputs;</li>
   <li>the classification of work outputs.</li>
 </outscope>

